Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":89,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice was born in 1170, in Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Roger Wrightington de Asheton. She died in 1278, in Pilkington, Lancashire, England, at the age of 108."},"et":{"1170–1278":"1170–1278","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1185–1275":"1185–1275","1195–1270":"1195–1270","1195–1278":"1195–1278","1275":"1275","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1278":"1278","about 1275":"umbes 1275","about 1185":"umbes 1185","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England","Chetham near Manchester or Pilkington, Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Pilkington, Lancashire, England":"Pilkington, Lancashire, England","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1170–1278":"1170–1278","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1185–1275":"1185–1275","1195–1270":"1195–1270","1195–1278":"1195–1278","1275":"1275","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1278":"1278","about 1275":"noin 1275","about 1185":"noin 1185","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England","Chetham near Manchester or Pilkington, Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Pilkington, Lancashire, England":"Pilkington, Lancashire, England","England":"England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1170–1278":"1170–1278","1165–1238":"1165–1238","1185–1275":"1185–1275","1195–1270":"1195–1270","1195–1278":"1195–1278","1275":"1275","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1278":"1278","about 1275":"environ 1275","about 1185":"environ 1185","Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire, England":"As